how do i know how far along i am if my pregnancy is following a miscarriage i had a miscarriage on i just found out i am pregnant again and it's only been weeks since my miscarriage i have still not had a period how can i determine how many weeks i am i would think that you probably ovulated weeks after your miscarriage usually your period returns weeks after m c so m c is looked at like your last period though this certainly may not be accurate an ultrasound your doctor can confirm your dates please also ignore misinformed and insensitive comments like those above by cassie as many women conceive straight after a m c and go onto have healthy babies i conceived in the first cycle after my m c and am now weeks along my ultrasound today shows a healthy baby boy pregnancy after m c is sometimes stressful enough without worrying that you have made a dangerous decision to fall pregnant again as cassie would have you believe please see your doctor get plenty of rest and good luck to you Pregnancy Miscarriage Obstetrics Abortion Fertility awareness Infertility In vitro fertilisation Intact dilation and extraction Prenatal diagnosis Premature birth Breastfeeding Urinary incontinence Days of our Lives Abortion in the United States Polycystic ovary syndrome Abortion debate Ovarian cyst Hex (TV Series) Childbirth Morning sickness Partial-birth abortion Birth control EastEnders Pregnancy test Habitual abortion Androgen insensitivity syndrome Spina bifida Friends Coeliac disease Infantilism Religion and abortion One Life to Live Stillbirth Breech birth Gynaecology Sex and the City Stomach cancer Multiple birth Dinah Marler Knots Landing The Tribe Twin Chemical abortion Cytomegalovirus Bipolar disorder Abortion in Canada Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Ectopic pregnancy History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Prostate cancer Guiding Light Psoriasis Folic acid Human height Sexual abstinence Anencephaly Louis XV of France Melanie Wilkes Antiphospholipid syndrome Midwifery 